Language: en

PHRoadSafetyIG

The official URL for this implementation guide is: 

https://build.fhir.org/ig/UPM-NTHC/PH-RoadSafetyIG/ImplementationGuide/example.fhir.ph.roadsafety

FHIR IG for road safety and health information in the Philippines

name: PHRoadSafetyIG
title: DRAFT PH Road Safety Implementation Guide
publisher: UP Manila - National Institutes of Health - National Telehealth Center

contact.name: UP Manila - National Institutes of Health - National Telehealth Center

description: FHIR IG for road safety and health information in the Philippines

extension.valueMarkdown: Automatically added as a dependency - all IGs depend on HL7 Terminology
Automatically added as a dependency - all IGs depend on the HL7 Extension Pack

resource.name: MDSRoadSafety Logical Model to FHIR Mapping
resource.description: Maps elements from the logical model to FHIR R4 resources. Generated by scripts/generate-conceptmap.js

resource.name: RS AllergyIntolerance
resource.description: Known allergies, substances and reactions.

resource.name: RS Bundle — EMS Submission
resource.description: Document Bundle for EMS Run Report submission. The first entry MUST be a Composition that organizes and references the other resources in the bundle (Patient, Encounter, Location, Observations, DocumentReference, Procedure, ServiceRequest, Task, Claim).

resource.name: RS Bundle — ONEISS Submission
resource.description: Document Bundle for Facility ONEISS submission. The first entry MUST be a Composition that organizes and references the other resources in the bundle (Patient, Encounter, Condition, Observations, DocumentReference, Procedure, ServiceRequest).

resource.name: RS Bundle — Post‑Crash Investigation
resource.description: Document Bundle for Post‑Crash investigation submission. The first entry MUST be a Composition that organizes and references post‑crash Observations and supporting DocumentReferences.

resource.name: RS Claim
resource.description: Claim information related to cost of care.

resource.name: RS Composition — EMS Submission
resource.description: Composition that organises an EMS run report. Sections MUST reference the other resources present in the corresponding document Bundle (Patient, Encounter, Location, Observations, DocumentReference, Procedure, ServiceRequest, Task, Claim).

resource.name: RS Composition — ONEISS Submission
resource.description: Composition that organises a facility (ONEISS) submission. Sections MUST reference the other resources present in the corresponding document Bundle (Patient, Encounter, Condition, Observations, DocumentReference, Procedure, ServiceRequest).

resource.name: RS Composition — Post‑Crash Investigation
resource.description: Composition that organises a Post‑Crash submission. Sections reference Observations and Documents related to post‑crash investigation (collision type, investigator presence, other risk factors, safety accessories, vehicle condition, CCTV, evidence documents).

resource.name: RS Condition
resource.description: Condition resource for RS IG that supports multiple coding systems, textual entries and use-case specific semantics (initial impression, final diagnosis, medical history) via code.coding slicing and category usage.

resource.name: RS Condition — External Cause (category)
resource.description: Captures the ICD-10 external cause axis as a Condition.category slice. Use in addition to the specific diagnosis code.

resource.name: RS Condition — Final Diagnosis
resource.description: Final diagnosis per CSV mapping.

resource.name: RS Condition — Initial Impression
resource.description: Enter the initial impression on the patient’s condition.

resource.name: RS Condition — Nature of Injury (category)
resource.description: Captures the ICD-10 nature-of-injury axis as a Condition.category slice. Use in addition to the specific diagnosis code.

resource.name: RS Condition — Problem
resource.description: Problem (finding) per CSV mapping.

resource.name: RS DocumentReference (Evidence)
resource.description: Evidence and post-crash documentation linked to the incident (e.g., cause of crash, party at fault, incident management logs, CCTV, shape files).

resource.name: RS Encounter
resource.description: Encounter for EMS run report / facility submission context. Captures incident number, type, timing, participants, disposition & transfer.

resource.name: RS Encounter Vehicle Used
resource.description: Identifier and type of transport vehicle used during an encounter.

resource.name: RS HealthcareService
resource.description: Healthcare services offered by organizations (e.g., EMS base, receiving facility clinics/units).

resource.name: RS Incident Location
resource.description: Location of incident; supports PH-Core address extensions and geolocation.

resource.name: RS MedicationStatement
resource.description: Current medications as codeable concepts or references where available.

resource.name: RS Minimum Dataset (MDS) Logical Model
resource.description: Abstract, sectioned logical model for the PH RS MDS covering incident, patient, encounter, clinical, vitals, injuries, evidence/documents, workflow, and finance. Elements mirror the CSV rows; mappings point to target FHIR elements for subsequent profiling.

resource.name: RS Observation
resource.description: Generic base Observation for RS data; specialized concept profiles below constrain code/value patterns.

resource.name: RS Observation - Abrasion
resource.description: Abrasion present; with optional site and details.

resource.name: RS Observation - Activity at Time of Incident
resource.description: Activity of the patient at time of incident; allow text fallback.

resource.name: RS Observation - Avulsion
resource.description: Avulsion present; with optional site and details.

resource.name: RS Observation - Blood Alcohol Concentration
resource.description: Blood alcohol concentration.

resource.name: RS Observation - Blood Pressure
resource.description: Blood pressure using component entries for systolic/diastolic.

resource.name: RS Observation - Body Temperature
resource.description: Body temperature.

resource.name: RS Observation - Call Source
resource.description: Call source description (free text).

resource.name: RS Observation - CCTV Available
resource.description: Availability of CCTV video.

resource.name: RS Observation - Clinical Remarks
resource.description: Clinical remarks/notes.

resource.name: RS Observation - Collision Type
resource.description: Collision type (Angle, Head-on, Rear end, Side swipe, etc.).

resource.name: RS Observation - Collision vs Non-Collision
resource.description: Indicates whether the incident was collision or non-collision.

resource.name: RS Observation - Concussion
resource.description: Concussion present; with site and details.

resource.name: RS Observation - Condition of Patient
resource.description: Overall condition of patient at assessment.

resource.name: RS Observation - Contusion
resource.description: Contusion present; with site and details.

resource.name: RS Observation - Cyanosis
resource.description: Cyanosis assessment.

resource.name: RS Observation - Date/Time of Injury
resource.description: DateTimestamp patient was seen at the health facility.

resource.name: RS Observation - External Cause: Bites/Stings
resource.description: Flag indicating bites/stings.

resource.name: RS Observation - External Cause: Burns
resource.description: Flag indicating burns as external cause.

resource.name: RS Observation - External Cause: Burns
resource.description: Flag indicating burns as external cause.

resource.name: RS Observation - External Cause: Chemical/Substance
resource.description: Observation for chemical/substance exposure.

resource.name: RS Observation - External Cause: Contact with Sharp Object
resource.description: Flag indicating sharp object cause.

resource.name: RS Observation - External Cause: Drowning
resource.description: Flag indicating drowning.

resource.name: RS Observation - External Cause: Exposure to Forces of Nature
resource.description: Flag indicating exposure to natural disaster/calamity.

resource.name: RS Observation - External Cause: Fall
resource.description: Flag indicating fall.

resource.name: RS Observation - External Cause: Firecracker
resource.description: Flag indicating firecracker-related cause.

resource.name: RS Observation - External Cause: Gunshot
resource.description: Flag indicating gunshot.

resource.name: RS Observation - External Cause: Hanging/Strangulation
resource.description: Flag indicating hanging/strangulation.

resource.name: RS Observation - External Cause: Mauling/Assault
resource.description: Flag indicating assault.

resource.name: RS Observation - External Cause: Other
resource.description: Flag indicating other external cause.

resource.name: RS Observation - External Cause: Sexual Assault/Abuse/Rape (Alleged)
resource.description: Flag indicating sexual assault.

resource.name: RS Observation - Fracture
resource.description: Fracture observation. Use valueCodeableConcept to indicate fracture type (e.g., open or closed). Sites captured in top-level bodySite and details in note.

resource.name: RS Observation - Glasgow Coma Scale
resource.description: GCS with components for eyes, verbal, motor; optional total score as integer.

resource.name: RS Observation - How Many Vehicles Involved
resource.description: Count of vehicles involved.

resource.name: RS Observation - Injury Intent
resource.description: Intent of injury (Unintentional, Intentional-self, Intentional-violence, Undetermined).

resource.name: RS Observation - Level of Consciousness (AVPU)
resource.description: Level of consciousness (e.g., AVPU).

resource.name: RS Observation - Mode of Transport to Facility
resource.description: Mode of transport to the hospital/facility; allow coded value with optional text for 'Others'.

resource.name: RS Observation - Multiple Injuries?
resource.description: Boolean flag indicating multiple injuries.

resource.name: RS Observation - Open Wound
resource.description: Open wound present; with site and details. Capture mechanism/type in a structured component (valueCodeableConcept with text).

resource.name: RS Observation - Other Risk Factors
resource.description: Other risk factors at the time of incident; allow text for 'Others'.

resource.name: RS Observation - Other Specified Injury
resource.description: Other specified injury present; capture type as valueCodeableConcept (text allowed) with optional site and details.

resource.name: RS Observation - Other Vehicle/Object Involved
resource.description: Other vehicle/object type involved; text for 'Others'.

resource.name: RS Observation - Outcome at Release
resource.description: Outcome at release from ER/OPD/RHU.

resource.name: RS Observation - Patient's Vehicle
resource.description: Type of vehicle used by patient; text for 'Others'.

resource.name: RS Observation - Place of Occurrence
resource.description: Place type where injury occurred; name can be carried in note when applicable.

resource.name: RS Observation - Position of Patient
resource.description: Seat/position (driver/front passenger/rear/pedestrian); text for 'Others'.

resource.name: RS Observation - Presence of Traffic Investigator
resource.description: Boolean presence/absence of traffic investigator.

resource.name: RS Observation - Priority Level (Urgency)
resource.description: System-generated urgency level per CAD/agency rules.

resource.name: RS Observation - Pulse Rate
resource.description: Pulse/heart rate in beats/min.

resource.name: RS Observation - Pupils
resource.description: Pupil size/reactivity summary.

resource.name: RS Observation - Referred By Facility
resource.description: Flag indicating patient was referred by another hospital/facility.

resource.name: RS Observation - Reported Complaint
resource.description: Free-text reported complaint. May or May not exactly be medical, could point to car crash, not a healthcare concern.

resource.name: RS Observation - Respiratory Rate
resource.description: Respiratory rate in breaths/min.

resource.name: RS Observation - Run Report Comments
resource.description: Enter other comment (s) regarding the case

resource.name: RS Observation - Safety Accessories
resource.description: Safety accessories present/used; allow text for 'Others'.

resource.name: RS Observation - Status on Arrival
resource.description: Status upon reaching facility/hospital.

resource.name: RS Observation - Timeline Date/Time
resource.description: Dispatch and transport timeline events capturing a precise date/time.

resource.name: RS Observation - Transferred From Facility
resource.description: Flag indicating patient transferred from another hospital/facility.

resource.name: RS Observation - Transport/Vehicular Accident
resource.description: Boolean flag indicating transport/vehicular accident.

resource.name: RS Observation - Traumatic Amputation
resource.description: Traumatic amputation present; with site and details.

resource.name: RS Observation - Triage Priority
resource.description: Triage category assigned at scene (e.g., Red/Yellow/Green/Black).

resource.name: RS Organization
resource.description: Organization profile for EMS providers and receiving facilities involved in RS encounters.

resource.name: RS Patient
resource.description: Patient demographics and identifiers for RS reporting; reuse PH-Core address extensions for barangay/city/province/region.

resource.name: RS Procedure
resource.description: Procedures related to incident/report (e.g., coordination with receiving hospital, psychosocial support, interventions).

resource.name: RS Procedure - Transport Coordination
resource.description: Procedure record indicating whether transport coordination with the receiving hospital was done.

resource.name: RS Service Location
resource.description: Facility/service delivery location. Type bound to HL7 v3 ServiceDeliveryLocationRoleType (e.g., ER, ward, clinic).

resource.name: RS ServiceRequest
resource.description: Requests or records related to refusal to admit and related workflow signals.

resource.name: RS Task
resource.description: Workflow tracking for report receipt, durations of delay, and sources of delays.

resource.name: RS VS - PSGC Barangay
resource.description: PSGC Barangay codes (managed externally).

resource.name: RS VS - PSGC City/Municipality
resource.description: PSGC City/Municipality codes (managed externally).

resource.name: RS VS - PSGC Province
resource.description: PSGC Province codes (managed externally).

resource.name: RS VS - PSGC Region
resource.description: PSGC Region codes (managed externally).

resource.name: SILPH - Activity (VS)
resource.description: SILPH Value Set for Patient Activity at the Time of Injury/Accident

resource.name: SILPH - Burns (VS)
resource.description: SILPH Value Set for Degree of Burn

resource.name: SILPH - Cyanosis (VS)
resource.description: SILPH Value Set for Presence of Cyanosis

resource.name: SILPH - Encounter Participant Role (VS)
resource.description: SILPH Value Set for EMS encounter participant roles documented on the run report.

resource.name: SILPH - External Cause of Burns (VS)
resource.description: SILPH Value Set for External Cause of Burns

resource.name: SILPH - External Cause of Drowning (VS)
resource.description: SILPH Value Set for External Cause of Drowning

resource.name: SILPH - Fracture Type (VS)
resource.description: SILPH Value Set for fracture type designation (open versus closed).

resource.name: SILPH - GCS - Eyes (VS)
resource.description: SILPH Value Set for GCS Eye Score

resource.name: SILPH - GCS - Motor (VS)
resource.description: SILPH Value Set for GCS Motor Score

resource.name: SILPH - GCS - Verbal (VS)
resource.description: SILPH Value Set for GCS Verbal Score

resource.name: SILPH - General Disposition (VS)
resource.description: SILPH Value Set for Inpatient and ER/Outpatient Visit Disposition

resource.name: SILPH - Injury Intent (VS)
resource.description: SILPH Value Set for Injury Intent

resource.name: SILPH - Inpatient Disposition (VS)
resource.description: SILPH Value Set for Inpatient Visit Disposition

resource.name: SILPH - Level of Consciousness (VS)
resource.description: SILPH Value Set for Level of Consciousness (AVPU) Score

resource.name: SILPH - List of Body Sites (VS)
resource.description: SILPH List of Body Sites

resource.name: SILPH - Mode of Transport (VS)
resource.description: SILPH Value Set for Mode of Transport of Patient to Healthcare Facility

resource.name: SILPH - Other Vehicle in Collision (VS)
resource.description: SILPH Value Set for Other Vehicle in Collision Accident

resource.name: SILPH - Outcome (VS)
resource.description: SILPH Value Set for Outcome

resource.name: SILPH - Outpatient/ER Disposition (VS)
resource.description: SILPH Value Set for Outpatient/ER Visit Disposition

resource.name: SILPH - Patient's Vehicle (VS)
resource.description: SILPH Value Set for Patient's Vehicle

resource.name: SILPH - Place of Occurrence (VS)
resource.description: SILPH Value Set for Place of Occurrence of Injury/Accident

resource.name: SILPH - Position of Patient (VS)
resource.description: SILPH Value Set for Position of Patient

resource.name: SILPH - PR - Quality (VS)
resource.description: SILPH Value Set for Pulse Quality

resource.name: SILPH - PR - Rhythm (VS)
resource.description: SILPH Value Set for Pulse Rhythm

resource.name: SILPH - Pupils (VS)
resource.description: SILPH Value Set for Pupil Reaction

resource.name: SILPH - Risk Factors (VS)
resource.description: SILPH Value Set for Risk Factors

resource.name: SILPH - RR - Breath Sounds (VS)
resource.description: SILPH Value Set for Breath Sounds

resource.name: SILPH - RR - Rhythm (VS)
resource.description: SILPH Value Set for Respiratory Rhythm

resource.name: SILPH - Safety Devices (VS)
resource.description: SILPH Value Set for Safety Devices

resource.name: SILPH - Sex (VS)
resource.description: SILPH Value Set for Sex

resource.name: SILPH - Status (VS)
resource.description: SILPH ValueSet for Patient Status, if Alive or Dead during Admission

resource.name: SILPH - Status if Alive (VS)
resource.description: SILPH Value Set for Patient Status, if patient is alive, specify if conscious or unconscious

resource.name: SILPH - Transport Accident Type (VS)
resource.description: SILPH Value Set for Transport Accident Type (Land, Water or Air)

resource.name: SILPH - Transport Accident: Collision or Noncollision (VS)
resource.description: SILPH Value Set for Transport Accident if Collision or Noncollision

resource.name: SILPH - Triage (VS)
resource.description: SILPH Value Set for Triage at Scene

resource.name: SILPH - Type of Patient (VS)
resource.description: SILPH Value Set for Type of Patient Encounter

resource.name: SILPH Road Safety Local Codes
resource.description: Compilation of local codes for SILPH Road Safety Project. Includes local codes for data element terminology mapping and local codes for value sets
